<article class="home-essay">
	<header class="article-header">
		<p class="eyebrow">Aelix</p>
		<h1>Notes from the dark forest.</h1>
		<p class="subtitle">Decision markets, practical agency, philosophy, and the occasional mechanism-design rabbit hole.</p>
	</header>

	<section class="article-body">
		<p><span class="newthought">Alex Janiak</span> writes about how people and institutions make decisions under uncertainty. The recurring obsession is simple: better world-models, tighter feedback loops, fewer unforced errors.</p>
		<p>This site keeps the essays close to the surface. No cards, no feeds pretending to be magazines, no algorithmic gloss. Just dated notes, arguments, and artifacts.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="archive-section">
		<h2>Latest</h2>
		{% set postslist = collections.posts | recentPosts(3) %}
		{% include "postslist.njk" %}
		<p class="archive-link"><a href="/blog/">All essays</a></p>
	</section>
</article>
